the two ends of the city♪

1052
00:43:27,392 --> 00:43:33,480
♪A lamp illuminates the day and night♪

1053
00:43:34,144 --> 00:43:40,570
♪A memory marks the passage of time♪

1054
00:43:41,664 --> 00:43:47,584
♪Always half lost, half happy♪

1055
00:43:49,056 --> 00:43:55,451
♪Who is not struggling yet optimistic♪

1056
00:43:56,243 --> 00:44:02,484
♪Whose life is not lively yet lonely♪

1057
00:44:03,232 --> 00:44:10,127
♪Whose story is intense yet ordinary♪

1058
00:44:10,752 --> 00:44:19,840
♪Always half perfunctory, half sincere♪

1059
00:44:20,615 --> 00:44:28,163
♪How many of us
have wandered through the chaos♪

1060
00:44:29,086 --> 00:44:35,200
♪How many nights
have you seen thunder and lightning♪

1061
00:44:35,456 --> 00:44:43,164
♪Looking left and right throughout time♪

1062
00:44:43,552 --> 00:44:49,355
♪I luckily turned the tide
when I met you♪

1063
00:44:49,992 --> 00:44:57,190
♪If youthful courage
had never been exhausted♪

1064
00:44:58,139 --> 00:45:04,480
♪Fearless simplicity
wouldn't have become a regret♪

1065
00:45:04,608 --> 00:45:12,251
♪In our long story,
nothing is a coincidence♪

1066
00:45:12,641 --> 00:45:17,628
♪The sky is always half night♪

1067
00:45:18,099 --> 00:45:22,560
♪Half dawn♪
